Lab classes are not good. You have a limited amount of time to complete a lab successfully, which means if you mess up due to an equipment malfunction, a miscommunication between partners, or just a mistake, you might not have enough time to do it over and just lose a ton of points. This makes the labs stressful, and it means we can't focus on exploring the concepts or even learning through experimentation because we have to work quickly to get the stupid thing turned in. It's somewhat unrealistic because non-lab classes allow everyone to learn at their own pace by studying at home, but here everyone is expected to be perfect in a few hours. Additionally, the classes are graded highly competitively, which is dumb because tons of people have to take them who aren't actual physics majors. A better idea would be to have a TA demonstrate the procedure of the lab up front and then have the students replicate it, and grade them on their process and analysis, not results. I honestly wish this class were better taught because I remember really enjoying lab days in high school physics.
